#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "Content Types"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:18
msgid "We are aligning Quarkus docs with the Di√°taxis documentation framework{fn-diataxis}, which defines a core content structure that addresses the different needs users have when consulting docs.  What follows is a brief summary of the different document types, but their site is worth a read if you want to understand more of the reasoning behind this classification."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "Concept guides (Explanation)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:23
msgid "Explanation is _discussion_ that clarifies and illuminates a particular topic. Explanation is _understanding-oriented_."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:25
msgid "Good concept guides:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:28
msgid "are about a topic, and aim to provide the reader with information that helps establish a deeper understanding of that topic."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:29
msgid "make connections to other things, if it helps explain the topic."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:30
msgid "provide background and context to help explain _why_."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:31
msgid "can consider alternatives or counter-examples, if it helps explain the topic."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:33
msgid "do things other parts of the documentation do not; rely on references, tutorials, and how-to guides to perform their roles."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "How-To guides"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:38
msgid "How-to guides are _directions_ that take the reader through the steps required to solve a real-world problem. How-to guides are _goal-oriented_."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:40
msgid "Good how-to guides:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:42
msgid "guide (walk-through) or demonstrate how to complete a task."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:43
msgid "assume you have enough context to begin the task."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:45
msgid "describes the concrete steps necessary to complete a task, but these steps could be in the middle of a larger task."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:46
msgid "do not explain concepts, they rely on other documents (like concepts) to do that."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:47
msgid "are adaptable to real-world use cases."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:48
msgid "are practical (rather than complete)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:50
#, no-wrap
msgid "Reference guides"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:53
msgid "Reference guides are _technical descriptions_ of the machinery and how to operate it. Reference material is _information-oriented_."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:55
msgid "Good reference guides:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:57
msgid "are concise and to the point. They state, describe, and inform."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:59
msgid "are consistent (to the extent possible) with other reference guides.  Following the template helps here."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:61
msgid "remain focused on describing their topic.  They don't explain or provide additional context from other sources."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:62
msgid "provide examples or illustrations that help readers understand what is being described."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:64
msgid "are kept up to date. While configuration reference material is generated, extension references that describe how configuration should be applied must be accurate to be useful."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:67
#, no-wrap
msgid "Tutorials"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:70
msgid "Tutorials are _lessons_ that take the reader by the hand through a series of steps to complete a project of some kind. Tutorials are _learning-oriented_."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:72
msgid "Good tutorials:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:74
msgid "provide a learning experience, giving the reader something they can do."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:75
msgid "get the reader started (they do not create an expert)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:76
msgid "provide the reader with concrete steps to follow that each have a comprehensible result."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:77
msgid "are reliable and consistent (they work for all users, every time)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:79
msgid "include only enough information to complete the task.  They delegate to other documentation types (concepts or reference) to provide additional context."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/doc-concepts.adoc:81
msgid "focus on one way of doing the task. Alternative approaches are explored in other document types (e.g. a how-to guide)."
msgstr ""
